value.name: Hokkaido - Wikipedia
value.snippet: Hokkaido (Japanese: 北海道, Hepburn: Hokkaidō, lit. 'Northern Sea Circuit', pronounced [ho̞k̚ka̠ido̞ː] pronunciation (help · info)) is Japan's second largest island and comprises the largest and northernmost prefecture, making up its own region. The Tsugaru Strait separates Hokkaidō from Honshu; the two islands are connected by the undersea railway Seikan Tunnel.
